reviews.review_text:
Thank you Charlie! Another nice SBD from Mr Charlie!  Thanks man!
This is a very nice 1980 show with Brent taking over and accepting his role as keyboardist for the best touring band ever!

nice sugaree This summer string had to be one of THE most undercirrculated tours.  Many of these shows didn't come on to the scene until much later in the digital game.

there is a lot of sound here.  A better than average sbd from any era.

peace

interested side note by  utopian glad to be able to hear it

jack straw has no jer guitar to very little

miss you jerry..... https://www.facebook.com/events/479366665408766/

	Jerome John "Jerry" Garcia (August 1, 1942 – August 9, 1995) 

Fellow deadheads and fans. Please share your stories, pictures, music, clippings anything that will help us all get through this day ♥

Where's Phil? Is it me, or is Phil completely missing?

(edit) Nevermind.  I hear him in Friend of the Devil.

Scarlet Jerry hits the pedal rite after the last line of Scarlet. Yes at some point going into Fire he hits it but I think this might be one of earliest I have heard him do that. Is rather nice. This is one of those shows that fly's under the radar because there are so many other smoking shows in 1980 late summer tour. Is also  one that takes getting use to listening to. 1st Wheel in sometime and 1st for Brent.  
 at some point someone could make a good matrix out of this one. Its a 3.5 stars show but I wont give it 3 because I hope others listen to it.
Five stars For DJ Dark Star Dan completely shutting down that know it all douchetroll kbmill. Great show

A Tiger in a trance those K.C. girls...
They throw in a little jam twist at the end of Circumstance for what was already a good set.
Sound issues during early Second Set
But In middle of Samson the yummy good sound hits.
And really the Scarlet>.Fire is just blazing.
If you are looking for a tight S>F with great sound.
This is it !!!
No jam out of Fire just straight into drums.
Weir ---pretty animated after Drumz,,, Going off the cuff during Trucking and talking about needing some medicine in a good way during Good lovin'
Not much extended exploration but the music is tight.
Beware the splices...
